    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow Mobile Gamers to Disable Pop-Up Offers",
        "additional_details": "We think this change would empower players, curb what we feel is predatory monetisation, and set a global standard for ethical gaming.\r\n\r\nWhy we think this matters:\r\n\u2022 Design: Constant pop-ups interrupt gameplay and can use pressure tactics that can lead to impulsive spending.\r\n\u2022 Consumer protection: These practices may target vulnerable users, including children, and could undermine informed choice.\r\n\u2022 Mental well-being: Reducing intrusive prompts can promote healthier gaming habits and a more enjoyable experience.",
        "background": "Make it a legal requirement for all mobile games available in the UK to include a setting that disables pop-up offers and purchase prompts.",
